main event: A witness reported observing a bright, cigar-shaped object moving at a high rate of speed near Sebring, Florida on January 17, 1967.
interesting points: The object was seen behind a C-121 aircraft by a nearby observer,The witness reported a low humming sound from the object,The weather conditions were reported as clear,The sighting was reported to the local authorities and the United States Air Force,The witness felt the object was not a conventional aircraft or balloon.
witness description: The observer was a civilian technician working for RCA, who observed the object with a clear view and documented the event cautiously.
